{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-publication-index-js","path":"/dp/122/farms-farmers-and-farming-a-perspective-through-data-and-behavioral-insights/","result":{"data":{"meta":{"siteMetadata":{"collections":[{"collection":"abridged","title":"aBRIDGEd","subtitle":"Making Research Accessible","url":"/abridged/","placeholder":null},{"collection":"thaipublica","title":"เศรษฐศาสตร์เข้า \"ท่า\"","subtitle":"Making Research Make Sense","url":"/thaipublica/","placeholder":null},{"collection":"pierspectives","title":"PIERspectives","subtitle":"Making Research Comprehensible","url":"/pierspectives/","placeholder":"pierspectives"},{"collection":"dp","title":"Discussion Paper","subtitle":"Making Research Inaccessible","url":"/dp/","placeholder":"dp"},{"collection":"members","title":"Members","subtitle":"Making Research Possible","url":"/pier-research-network/","placeholder":null},{"collection":"announcements","title":"Announcements","subtitle":"Making Research Public","url":"/announcements/","placeholder":"announcements"},{"collection":"blog","title":"PIER Blog","subtitle":"Making Research Public","url":"/blog/","placeholder":"blog"},{"collection":"conferences","title":"Conferences","subtitle":"Making Research Big","url":"/conferences/","placeholder":"conferences"},{"collection":"workshops","title":"Workshops and Forums","subtitle":"Making Research Work","url":"/workshops/","placeholder":"seminars"},{"collection":"seminars","title":"PIER Economic Seminars","subtitle":"Making Research Better","url":"/seminars/","placeholder":"seminars"},{"collection":"exchange","title":"PIER Research Exchange","subtitle":"Making Research Exchangable","url":"/exchange/","placeholder":"seminars"}],"series":[{"series":"Industry Transformation","placeholder":"industry-transformation"},{"series":"Public Economics","placeholder":"public-economics"}]}},"mdx":{"body":"var _excluded = [\"components\"];\n\nfunction _extends() { _extends = Object.assign || function (target) { for (var i = 1; i < arguments.length; i++) { var source = arguments[i]; for (var key in source) { if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(source, key)) { target[key] = source[key]; } } } return target; }; return _extends.apply(this, arguments); }\n\nfunction _objectWithoutProperties(source, excluded) { if (source == null) return {}; var target = _objectWithoutPropertiesLoose(source, excluded); var key, i; if (Object.getOwnPropertySymbols) { var sourceSymbolKeys = Object.getOwnPropertySymbols(source); for (i = 0; i < sourceSymbolKeys.length; i++) { key = sourceSymbolKeys[i]; if (excluded.indexOf(key) >= 0) continue; if (!Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable.call(source, key)) continue; target[key] = source[key]; } } return target; }\n\nfunction _objectWithoutPropertiesLoose(source, excluded) { if (source == null) return {}; var target = {}; var sourceKeys = Object.keys(source); var key, i; for (i = 0; i < sourceKeys.length; i++) { key = sourceKeys[i]; if (excluded.indexOf(key) >= 0) continue; target[key] = source[key]; } return target; }\n\n/* @jsxRuntime classic */\n\n/* @jsx mdx */\nvar _frontmatter = {\n  \"id\": \"122\",\n  \"title\": \"Farms, Farmers and Farming: A Perspective through Data and Behavioral Insights\",\n  \"authors\": [\"Witsanu Attavanich\", \"Sommarat Chantarat\", \"Jirath Chenphuengpawn\", \"Phumsith Mahasuweerachai\", \"Kannika Thampanishvong\"],\n  \"date\": \"2019-12-25T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"pdf\": \"pier_dp_122.pdf\"\n};\nvar layoutProps = {\n  _frontmatter: _frontmatter\n};\nvar MDXLayout = \"wrapper\";\nreturn function MDXContent(_ref) {\n  var components = _ref.components,\n      props = _objectWithoutProperties(_ref, _excluded);\n\n  return mdx(MDXLayout, _extends({}, layoutProps, props, {\n    components: components,\n    mdxType: \"MDXLayout\"\n  }), mdx(\"p\", null, \"This paper aims to contribute to a better understanding of Thai agriculture, the sector that currently employs about one third of the country\\u2019s labor force. We first draw out key stylized facts on our farms, farmers and farming from various granular farmer\\u2019s administrative data sets that allow us to observe what has happened at the plot, labor and household levels over the past decade, and cover more than 90% of farmers nationwide. We then use a stochastic frontier analysis to identify key drivers of household\\u2019s agricultural productivity, and project the potential productivity impacts from the four key driving factors: climate change, aging, irrigation and technology for every tambon nationwide. A meta-analysis is then used to illustrate the landscape of technological development throughout the rice value chain in Thailand. Finally, we use lab in the field experiments to understand behavioral insights that underly farmer\\u2019s incentives particularly in the context of technological adoption. Our results shed some lights on how to design, prioritize and implement policies to ensure that our farmers stay competitive, resilient and sustainable.\"));\n}\n;\nMDXContent.isMDXComponent = true;","fields":{"slug":"/dp/122/farms-farmers-and-farming-a-perspective-through-data-and-behavioral-insights/","collection":"dp","shorturl":"/dp/122/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Farms, Farmers and Farming: A Perspective through Data and Behavioral Insights","subtitle":null,"series":null,"authors":["Witsanu Attavanich","Sommarat Chantarat","Jirath Chenphuengpawn","Phumsith Mahasuweerachai","Kannika Thampanishvong"],"date":"2019-12-25T00:00:00.000Z","updated":null,"cover":null,"excerpt":null,"bibliography":null,"topics":null,"tags":null,"layout":null,"pdf":{"publicURL":"/static/9dd3ef22ab1a0f4774439f07fe5d5cb6/pier_dp_122.pdf"}},"authors":[{"frontmatter":{"memberid":"Jirath Chenphuengpawn","title":"Jirath Chenphuengpawn","org":"bot","email":"JirathC@bot.or.th","image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8f8f8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/e7eeef045cd5b0692cfe25f939e478f3/dd515/profile.jpg","srcSet